      answer:
        'Yes, but it quickly gets to be at a lesser amount. Down at 100 to 150\nfeet, the wave motion from the typical swells is mostly or completely\ngone. The boat is much steadier. However, you probably will be aware of\nup and down angles during larger changes in depth. Those are due to\noperation of the boat and are separate from wave action.\nShortly after leaving port, the captain will usually do "angles and\ndangles." This is normally announced in advance. The captain would then\norder depth changes with larger up and down angles. This is done to\nshake loose any equipment and supplies that aren\'t stored properly. This\nprovides an opportunity to store everything properly before it can\nbecome a problem.',
